77.5.4. Software / System test
System testing is a type of testing conducted on a complete integrated system to evaluate the system&#x2019;s compliance with its specified requirements. This is a type of black-box testing of the complete software in the target system. The most important factor in successful system testing is that the environmental conditions for the software have to be as realistic as possible (complete original hardware in the destination environment).
